<TITLE> Senator Kennedy has brain tumour, hospital says </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WASHINGTON, May 20 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Massachusetts Sen. Edward Kennedy has a malignant brain tumor, his doctors said on Tuesday. Kennedy has a glioma and will require chemotherapy and radiation therapy, neurologist Dr. Lee Schwamm of Massachusetts General Hospital, and Dr. Larry Ronan, a primary physician there, said in a statement. Kennedy has been in the hospital since he had a seizure on Saturday.
